@jteagles: this is about to upgrade to hadoop 3.2.2, I think a 100% green testing would mean that we're compatible with it (I ran mvn clean install locally too, no failures)
https://ci-hadoop.apache.org/job/tez-multibranch/job/PR-126/1/testReport/

this upgrade would make sense for Tez 0.10.1, and then we can consider cutting off branch-0.10 before starting for hadoop 3.3 support

> @jteagles: what do you think about this? TestShuffleHandlerJobs passes with this precommit job (as well as locally)
> if this is committed, I can try to proceed with Hadoop 3.3.x upgrade

@jteagles: could you please take a look? thanks

@medb : I can see the shade plugin bump solved the shading problem
however there are 3 commits, from which I don't get this one: https://github.com/apache/tez/pull/74/commits/00134f885047a9a9797e877699a617f29d3a60a9
could you please squash your commits to have the final one that we can merge into master from this PR?
